note1: we can create an logback-spring.xml extra xml file inside the folder where the jar file contains then we can use this xml file to override the logback.xml file by using the bellow cmd
note2: if we have an other application.properties(any property files) file then we can put that file inside the folder that where the jar contains then that file will taken by the jar file, this is an default behaviour of spring boot 

java -jar external-terminal-app-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar --logging.config=logback-spring.xml


